## Usage

```bash
# Reset database with seeds
npm run db:reset

# Run seeds only (no migrations)
npm run db:seed

# Create new seed file
touch supabase/seeds/04-your-data.sql
# Then update supabase/config.toml to include it
```

## Adding New Seed Files

1. Create file: `04-your-data.sql`
2. Add to `supabase/config.toml`:
   ```toml
   [db]
   seed_sql_paths = [
     "seed.sql",
     "seeds/01-users.sql",
     "seeds/02-profiles.sql",
     "seeds/03-example-data.sql",
     "seeds/04-your-data.sql"
   ]
   ```
3. Run `npm run db:reset`

## Best Practices

- ✅ Use consistent UUIDs (easier to reference across files)
- ✅ Add comments explaining data purpose
- ✅ Keep minimal (only what's needed for dev)
- ✅ Use fake but realistic data
- ❌ Never include production data
- ❌ Don't create thousands of records (slow)

